  "category_subtitle": "Learn how to count times or occurrences in Japanese using 回",
  "category_detail": "<b>Counting Occurrences in Japanese</b><br><br>In Japanese, the counter <b>「回」(かい / kai)</b> is used to count how many times something happens.<br><br>This counter is used for events, actions, repetitions, experiences, and occurrences.<br><br><b>Examples</b><br><span class=\"example\">一回</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いっかい / ikkai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">三回</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんかい / sankai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">六回</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ろっかい / rokkai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">十回</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっかい / jukkai)</span><br><br><b>Common Usage</b><br><span class=\"example\">日本に三回行きました。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(nihon ni sankai ikimashita)</span><br>Meaning: I went to Japan three times.<br><br><span class=\"example\">この映画を二回見ました。</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(kono eiga o nikai mimashita)</span><br>Meaning: I watched this movie twice.<br><br><b>Important Note</b><br>Some numbers change pronunciation because of sound changes, such as <b>1, 6, 8, and 10</b>.",
